The '''Ace Matara Power Station''' was a {{Nowrap|25-[[megawatt]]}} power station located in [[Matara, Sri Lanka]]. During its operations from 2002-2012, the plant utilized four {{Nowrap|6.3 MW}} {{Nowrap|[[Wärtsilä]] 18V32LN}} generating units. The plant was decommissioned in 2012 after its 10-year [[Power Purchase Agreement|PPA]] expired and recommissioned in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=Diesel and Gas-Engine Power Plants in Sri Lanka|url=http://www.industcards.com/ic-sri-lanka.htm|publisher=Industcards.com|accessdate=10 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=We decided to close down 03 thermal power generation plants that supplied electricity to the Ceylon Electricity Board|url=http://powermin.gov.lk/english/?page_id=3711|publisher=[[Ministry of Power and Energy]]|accessdate=10 November 2015|date=15 May 2015}}</ref> {{Clear}}
